The paper proposes a method for combining model-free and model-based approaches for exploration in reinforcement learning. This involves the use of Q-ensembles, which are commonly used in the field of machine learning (cs.LG), and encoder-decoder models for next frame prediction (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of trajectory memory, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper's focus on exploration and reinforcement learning suggests that it could also be relevant to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
